.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-INTERACTIVE 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-interactive \- run the interactive hunk review interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch interactive
.br
.B git-stage-batch -i
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B interactive
starts a continuous hunk-by-hunk interface similar to
.BR "git add -p" .
It starts a session, displays the selected hunk with progress information, and
shows a menu of actions.
.SH ACTIONS
.TP
.B i, include
Stage the selected hunk and advance.
.TP
.B s, skip
Skip the selected hunk and advance.
.TP
.B d, discard
Discard the selected hunk after confirmation.
.TP
.B a, again
Start another pass over skipped hunks.
.TP
.B l, lines
Open the line-selection submenu.
.TP
.B f, file
Open file-level include and skip actions.
.TP
.B q, quit
Exit interactive mode.
.TP
.B !, command
Run a shell command in the repository root.
.TP
.B ?, help
Display interactive help.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-include (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-skip (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-discard (1)
